Others: Karl-Anthony Towns returned from a two-game absence to score 27 points and grab 13 rebounds, leading the New York Knicks to a 112-98 victory over the Toronto Raptors.
Josh Hart also had an efficient night, making 9-of-14 shots, as he remained unbeaten in four games against his former team.
OG Anunoby also had an efficient night, making 8-of-13 shots, as the Knicks front court made up for their backcourt's shooting woes.

Jalen Brunson and Mikal Bridges finished in double figures with 13 and 10 points, respectively, but they combined for a rough 9-of-31 shooting night, including a 3-of-15 stinker from the 3-point line.
